      <!-- What is it? -->
      <section class="mt-4">
        <h2>What is Codeplug App?</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Codeplug App is a web-based tool for managing two-way radio programming data.
          It serves as a "Rosetta Stone" for codeplugs, allowing you to create your radio
          configuration once and export it to multiple radio-specific formats.
        </p>
        <p>
          Instead of recreating your codeplug for each radio model you own, define your channels,
          zones, systems, and talkgroups in a universal format, then export to CSV files compatible
          with Motorola CPS, CHIRP, Baofeng software, and dozens of other programming tools.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Purpose & Goals -->
      <section class="mt-5">
        <h2>Purpose & Goals</h2>
        <p>
          The goal of Codeplug App is to simplify radio programming for ham radio operators and
          radio programmers who work with multiple radio types. Key objectives include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Eliminate duplicate work when programming multiple radios</li>
          <li>Provide a centralized database of repeaters and talkgroups</li>
          <li>Support community sharing of codeplug configurations</li>
          <li>Make radio programming accessible to new operators</li>
          <li>Maintain compatibility with dozens of radio models and software packages</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

